The paper discusses the use of energy-based models (EBMs) for model-based planning in reinforcement learning (RL), which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. Based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving sample efficiency and generalization in RL through the use of EBMs. The paper also mentions the use of maximum entropy state inference and generating diverse state space plans, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of EBMs for intentionally planned state exploration, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper mentions the use of EBMs for online learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
